The paper is about image segmentation, which is a classic topic in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper covers a wide range of segmentation topics, including recent developments in superpixel, interactive methods, object proposals, semantic image parsing, and image cosegmentation, which are all related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses influential datasets and evaluation metrics, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
